						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>ACHYUTADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1534 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1456, Jaya, Vaiśā(kha), śu. 11, Saturday, corresponding to April 24, Friday 1534 A.D., f.d.t. °59.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged and mutilated. Registers the gift of a tax, called <hi rend="italic">Dommaripannu</hi> to the temple of Gōpinātha on the day of <hi rend="italic">yēkādaśī</hi> for the merit of certain communities during the reigning period of Achyutadēvarāya.</p>						

						</summary>
